               <p>I belong to the division at Chatham, I knew 
               <persName id="t17840421-16-person286">
                  Charles
                   Creswell
               <interp inst="t17840421-16-person286" type="surname" value="Creswell"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840421-16-person286" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840421-16-person286" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , he went on board the Lizard frigate with me, I was on board from the 6th of April 1781, to the 13th of March 1782.</p>
               <p>Look at that man, is that him? - That is not the man.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was led into it innocently by a man that belonged to the ship; I was made a prisoner, and they let the other men go.</p>
               <p>
