               <p>He was humbly recommended to mercy by the Jury.</p>
               <p>Court. I do verily believe that this man's name was a very unfortunate thing to him; I think there may be circumstances of alleviation in this poor man's case.</p>

               <p>Tried by the second London Jury, before Mr. JUSTICE NARES.</p>
